The paper deals with the joint design of storage and transmission policies in content delivery networks, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper introduces the problem of secretive coded caching, which involves privacy and security concerns, making it relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes a feasible scheme for the secretive coded caching problem, which involves network optimization and resource allocation, making it relevant to the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
